1
00:03:40,194 --> 00:03:42,913
Somebody's pullin' me close to the ground.

2
00:03:44,354 --> 00:03:46,470
I can sense, but I can't see.

3
00:03:47,954 --> 00:03:50,627
I ain't panicked. I been here before.

4
00:03:50,994 --> 00:03:53,667
Same as when I got popped
on 104th Street.

5
00:03:54,954 --> 00:03:57,422
Don't take me to no hospital, please.

6
00:03:57,554 --> 00:04:00,193
Fuckin' emergency rooms
don't save nobody.

7
00:04:00,514 --> 00:04:02,823
Son of a bitches always pop you
at midnight...

8
00:04:02,994 --> 00:04:06,384
...when all they got is a Chinese intern
with a dull spoon.

9
00:04:07,514 --> 00:04:12,065
Look at these suckers scramblin' around.
What for?

10
00:04:12,714 --> 00:04:16,150
My Puerto Rican ass ain't supposed
to have made it this far.

11
00:04:16,874 --> 00:04:19,786
Most of my crew got washed
a long time ago.

12
00:04:24,714 --> 00:04:28,832
Don't worry. My heart, it don't ever quit.

13
00:04:30,074 --> 00:04:32,065
I ain't ready to check out.

14
00:04:41,794 --> 00:04:44,308
Seems like I just got out of thejoint.

15
00:04:44,634 --> 00:04:48,513
Stood up in front of that judge,
and told him what was who.

16
00:04:51,354 --> 00:04:54,551
Now I ain't sayin' that my way
would have been different...

17
00:04:54,674 --> 00:04:58,872
...had my mother been alive when I was
a kid, 'cause that's all you hear in the joint.

18
00:04:58,954 --> 00:05:02,708
"I didn't have a chance." No. Bullshit.

19
00:05:03,034 --> 00:05:07,903
I was already a mean little bastard
while my mother was alive, and I know it.

20
00:05:07,994 --> 00:05:09,746
But I learned about women from her.

21
00:05:09,834 --> 00:05:13,509
Mr. Brigante, there are 56 cases
on the court's docket for this morning.

22
00:05:13,594 --> 00:05:15,027
Why am I listening to this?

23
00:05:15,154 --> 00:05:17,714
Your Honor, Mr. Brigante
is understandably excited...

24
00:05:17,794 --> 00:05:20,672
...having been vindicated
after five years of incarceration.

25
00:05:20,754 --> 00:05:22,551
There's no vindication here, counselor.

26
00:05:22,674 --> 00:05:25,234
Or absolution, or benediction,
or anything...

27
00:05:25,474 --> 00:05:27,988
...other than an incredible
convergence of circumstances...

28
00:05:28,074 --> 00:05:30,429
...which you've exploited
to your client's benefit.

29
00:05:30,514 --> 00:05:32,903
Your Honor, these circumstances
that you speak of...

30
00:05:32,994 --> 00:05:35,713
...include illegal wiretaps
and tainted evidence.

31
00:05:35,794 --> 00:05:38,752
This is a classic
"fruit of the poisoned tree" situation.

32
00:05:38,834 --> 00:05:41,348
I think after five years
of unjust incarceration...

33
00:05:41,434 --> 00:05:45,222
...it's reasonable to request Mr. Brigante
be indulged his right to speak.

34
00:05:45,394 --> 00:05:47,464
Okay, Mr. Brigante, I'm all ears.

35
00:05:48,474 --> 00:05:49,793
Your Honor...

36
00:05:50,354 --> 00:05:52,026
...with all due respect...

37
00:05:52,714 --> 00:05:55,706
...past and present,
and without further to-do.

38
00:05:57,274 --> 00:06:01,790
Let me assure this court that
I am through walkin' on the wild side.

39
00:06:02,794 --> 00:06:04,705
That's all I've been tryin' to tell you.

40
00:06:04,834 --> 00:06:09,191
I have been sick with the social ills
known in the ghetto...

41
00:06:09,714 --> 00:06:14,230
...but my time in the sterling
correctional facilities...

42
00:06:14,714 --> 00:06:18,912
...of Green Haven and Sing Sing
has not been in vain. I've been cured!

43
00:06:19,794 --> 00:06:22,149
Born again, like the Watergaters.

44
00:06:22,394 --> 00:06:25,704
I know you heard this rap before.
Your Honor, I mean it.

45
00:06:25,994 --> 00:06:28,110
This is the truth. I changed.

46
00:06:28,754 --> 00:06:31,746
I changed and it didn't take no 30 years...

47
00:06:31,834 --> 00:06:34,985
...like Your Honor thought, but only five.

48
00:06:35,634 --> 00:06:38,148
That's right, sir. Five years.

49
00:06:38,554 --> 00:06:41,591
And look at me. Completely rehabilitated...

50
00:06:41,994 --> 00:06:47,352
...reinvigorated, reassimilated,
and finally gonna be relocated.

51
00:06:47,594 --> 00:06:49,789
And I want to thank
a lot of people for that.

52
00:06:49,874 --> 00:06:52,513
I look over there and I see
that man there, Mr. Norwalk.

53
00:06:52,794 --> 00:06:56,548
I want to thank you, sir,
for making the tapes in an illegal fashion.

54
00:06:57,354 --> 00:07:02,633
I would like to thank the Court of Appeals
for reversing you, Your Honor.

55
00:07:03,114 --> 00:07:04,786
And I want to thank...

56
00:07:04,874 --> 00:07:08,992
...AImighty God, without whom
no case gets tossed.

57
00:07:09,354 --> 00:07:12,903
- I can't believe this.
- I must have forgot. How could I forget...

58
00:07:13,434 --> 00:07:16,392
...my dear, close friend and lawyer...

59
00:07:17,114 --> 00:07:21,744
...David Kleinfeld,
who never gave up on me...

60
00:07:22,154 --> 00:07:23,906
...through everything, thick and thin.

61
00:07:23,994 --> 00:07:26,747
- Why don't you just stand up?
- I'm sorry.

62
00:07:27,074 --> 00:07:29,542
- Mr. Brigante!
- Davey Kleinfeld.

63
00:07:29,834 --> 00:07:32,029
You're not accepting an award.

64
00:07:33,594 --> 00:07:35,152
Court of Appeals' decision...

65
00:07:36,474 --> 00:07:40,467
...and the District Attorney's
unfortunate investigative techniques...

66
00:07:41,794 --> 00:07:45,309
...now devolve upon me the painful duty
of unleashing upon society...

67
00:07:45,394 --> 00:07:48,625
...a reputed assassin
and convicted purveyor of narcotics.

68
00:07:48,834 --> 00:07:51,746
No. Never convicted on no dope.

69
00:07:52,794 --> 00:07:56,469
The indictment is dismissed.
Prisoner is discharged. Call the next case.

70
00:07:57,114 --> 00:07:59,230
- I'm indebted to you.
- Okay.

71
00:07:59,794 --> 00:08:01,022
I feel like I won.

72
00:08:01,114 --> 00:08:03,070
Excuse me. Congratulations.

73
00:08:05,994 --> 00:08:09,145
- No hard feelings, right?
- I'll be seeing you, Brigante.

74
00:08:13,434 --> 00:08:15,664
That was some line of crap
you handed him in there.

75
00:08:15,794 --> 00:08:19,264
That was no line of crap, man.
I meant every word I said.

76
00:08:20,154 --> 00:08:22,543
You don't understand. You don't get it.

77
00:08:22,874 --> 00:08:25,434
I'm a free man,
and I don't mean just out of jail.

78
00:08:25,514 --> 00:08:29,268
"I am free at last, free at last...

79
00:08:29,794 --> 00:08:34,914
- "...thank God Almighty, I am free at last!"
- I gotta work here. Save your energy.

80
00:08:34,994 --> 00:08:37,383
Wait till you see what I got
lined up for tonight.

81
00:08:47,954 --> 00:08:51,390
So what are you gonna do for money?
Hook up with Rolando again?

82
00:08:51,514 --> 00:08:54,392
I told you, I ain't goin' back to the street.

83
00:08:56,114 --> 00:08:58,344
Twenty-five years I worked that sucker.

84
00:08:58,834 --> 00:09:00,870
What do I got to show for it? Squat.

85
00:09:00,954 --> 00:09:03,422
You dancing with me
or you dancing with him?

86
00:09:03,714 --> 00:09:06,353
What does that mean,
"I ain't goin' back on the street"?

87
00:09:06,434 --> 00:09:08,584
What else do you know how to do?

88
00:09:09,434 --> 00:09:11,868
- I got plans, baby.
- Talk to me.

89
00:09:13,234 --> 00:09:16,351
'Cause you can dance
with him if you wanna.

90
00:09:17,194 --> 00:09:20,152
I know Dave since he was
just out of law school.

91
00:09:20,834 --> 00:09:23,746
He was workin' as a clerk
for a big mob lawyer.

92
00:09:24,354 --> 00:09:28,393
Kept a tire iron under the seat of his car,
tried like hell not to look scared...

93
00:09:28,474 --> 00:09:30,465
...by all his wise guy clients.

94
00:09:31,154 --> 00:09:34,226
But Davey Kleinfeld,
he ain't scared no more.

95
00:09:37,434 --> 00:09:38,913
So look at you.

96
00:09:40,154 --> 00:09:42,190
You really made something of your life.

97
00:09:42,354 --> 00:09:45,471
You put me in business.
All my first clients came through you.

98
00:09:45,674 --> 00:09:47,824
As I say, you know, top drawer.

99
00:09:48,114 --> 00:09:50,025
You're top drawer, Davey.

100
00:09:50,674 --> 00:09:51,902
Man.

101
00:09:52,674 --> 00:09:56,349
Listen, I got something for you.
You remember Saso?

102
00:09:56,834 --> 00:09:58,187
Saso. Yeah.

103
00:09:58,274 --> 00:10:00,390
Fat guy, had the Argentine place
on Madison.

104
00:10:00,634 --> 00:10:03,467
He bought the lease on this bankrupt disco.
Beautiful place.

105
00:10:03,554 --> 00:10:05,704
I got some investors together
and we backed him.

106
00:10:05,794 --> 00:10:07,591
I got $50,000 in the place.

107
00:10:07,674 --> 00:10:11,064
Problem is Saso. He's been shakin' the till,
payin' off gambling debts.

108
00:10:11,154 --> 00:10:14,146
He says he doesn't get $25,000,
he's gonna lose his lease.

109
00:10:14,274 --> 00:10:16,629
I like the place. I go there sometimes.

110
00:10:16,714 --> 00:10:19,274
The money's no big deal.
I don't mind puttin' it in...

111
00:10:19,354 --> 00:10:23,313
...as long as I know there's someone there
who's gonna run the place straight, clean.

112
00:10:23,634 --> 00:10:24,623
Me?

113
00:10:25,554 --> 00:10:27,863
I owned clubs. I never ran 'em.

114
00:10:28,434 --> 00:10:30,994
What's the big deal?
You step in, straighten things out...

115
00:10:31,074 --> 00:10:33,827
...you take a salary, a chunk of the profits.
- Please.

116
00:10:35,594 --> 00:10:37,903
You've done enough already for me.

117
00:10:38,114 --> 00:10:40,264
You call it a favor between friends.

118
00:10:40,394 --> 00:10:42,112
No favor. I owe you.

119
00:10:42,714 --> 00:10:45,023
Favor gonna kill you faster than a bullet.

120
00:10:54,874 --> 00:10:56,466
You saved my life.

121
00:10:58,714 --> 00:11:00,306
You saved my life, Dave.

122
00:11:00,994 --> 00:11:03,110
Thirty years. You know what that is?

123
00:11:03,874 --> 00:11:07,753
I was dead. I was buried.
I was under the ground.

124
00:11:09,234 --> 00:11:10,428
You dug me up.

125
00:11:14,994 --> 00:11:17,189
I don't know what to say to you.

126
00:11:18,434 --> 00:11:20,152
I just don't know what to say.

127
00:11:20,314 --> 00:11:21,633
Say you love me.

128
00:11:22,314 --> 00:11:23,463
I love you.

129
00:11:24,514 --> 00:11:27,347
If you was a broad, I'd marry you.

130
00:11:28,274 --> 00:11:30,265
- My boy.
- I bet you would.

131
00:11:30,514 --> 00:11:32,823
Who's that? Well, you know...

132
00:11:33,434 --> 00:11:36,585
Look, we're going to the ladies' room.

133
00:11:37,394 --> 00:11:38,429
Goodbye, you two.

134
00:11:38,514 --> 00:11:40,744
- Well, somebody's got to.
- Bye-bye.

135
00:11:49,354 --> 00:11:51,310
So, what are these plans?

136
00:11:52,234 --> 00:11:54,429
What's the big goddamn secret?

137
00:12:00,754 --> 00:12:03,188
You remember a guy named Clyde Bassie?

138
00:12:03,554 --> 00:12:05,670
Got out of the joint a couple of years ago.

139
00:12:06,474 --> 00:12:10,023
He went down to the Bahamas,
Paradise Island...

140
00:12:11,474 --> 00:12:13,783
...and he got this car rental place.

141
00:12:14,114 --> 00:12:16,423
He used to talk about it
all the time in the can.

142
00:12:16,554 --> 00:12:19,352
He got out, he went down there,
put it together.

143
00:12:19,514 --> 00:12:22,426
And it's doin' good. Real good.

144
00:12:23,074 --> 00:12:25,269
I mean, like, it's makin' money.

145
00:12:26,314 --> 00:12:29,863
Couple of months ago
he wrote me and he said...

146
00:12:30,394 --> 00:12:33,830
...I could buy in any time
I got $75,000 together.

147
00:12:39,754 --> 00:12:41,472
You're gonna rent cars.

148
00:12:49,834 --> 00:12:51,426
What are you laughing at?

149
00:12:54,954 --> 00:12:58,071
- You're gonna rent cars.
- That's right. I know a lot about cars.

150
00:12:58,354 --> 00:13:00,709
I've been stealing 'em since I was 14.

151
00:13:01,474 --> 00:13:02,987
Look at him laugh.

152
00:13:09,234 --> 00:13:10,826
I'll tell you something.

153
00:13:11,634 --> 00:13:14,432
Car rental guys don't get killed that much.

154
00:13:17,074 --> 00:13:19,508
And where are you gonna get the $75,000?

155
00:13:20,354 --> 00:13:23,664
I don't know. Maybe some rich relative
dies and leaves it to me.

156
00:13:25,394 --> 00:13:28,352
It's a dream, Dave. You gotta dream, baby.

157
00:13:29,634 --> 00:13:32,228
You got it all worked out, Carlito.
Here's to you.

158
00:13:35,074 --> 00:13:36,951
So here's me back on the street.

159
00:13:37,714 --> 00:13:40,433
Third Sunday in August.
Old Timer's Day in the barrio.

160
00:13:40,514 --> 00:13:43,153
- When did you get out, papi?
- A couple of days ago.

161
00:13:43,514 --> 00:13:44,742
Nothin' left.

162
00:13:44,914 --> 00:13:48,873
Like them old cowboy movies,
but instead of tumbleweed and cow dung...

163
00:13:49,274 --> 00:13:51,913
...we got stripped car wrecks and dog shit.

164
00:13:52,394 --> 00:13:54,066
A lot of new faces?

165
00:13:54,714 --> 00:13:57,353
These young guys, I don't recognize 'em.

166
00:13:59,754 --> 00:14:01,745
Mi barrio ya no existe.

167
00:14:02,794 --> 00:14:05,433
Carlito, man, Death Valley out here, man.

168
00:14:05,834 --> 00:14:09,622
Mira, you know me, I take to the street
with any of these motherfuckers, man.

169
00:14:09,914 --> 00:14:13,350
But these new kids nowadays, man,
they got no respect for human life.

170
00:14:13,434 --> 00:14:16,107
They shotgun you,
just to see you fly up in the air.

171
00:14:16,194 --> 00:14:18,185
'Chacho, you're better off in jail.

172
00:14:18,314 --> 00:14:20,350
I don't even go
up to black Harlem no more.

173
00:14:20,434 --> 00:14:23,107
They're fuckin' crazy up there.
Remember Victor?

174
00:14:23,594 --> 00:14:26,666
- Victor, with the beard.
- He got shot right in front of the High.

175
00:14:26,754 --> 00:14:29,188
Right in front of fuckin' Patrick Henry High.

176
00:14:29,474 --> 00:14:32,272
- Y Lalin, you know him.
- Lalin Miasso. What happened to him?

177
00:14:32,354 --> 00:14:35,949
Lalin's doin' thirty years in Attica, man.
Thirty years!

178
00:14:39,234 --> 00:14:41,828
Walberto! Check it out. Mira who's here.

179
00:14:41,954 --> 00:14:43,865
- Mira, eso. Oye.
- Hey, Wally.

180
00:14:43,954 --> 00:14:46,707
- Heavy-duty.
- Good to see you.

181
00:14:47,194 --> 00:14:49,628
I've been looking all over for you.

182
00:14:50,154 --> 00:14:52,873
Should have figured
I'd find you walking around up here...

183
00:14:52,954 --> 00:14:56,390
...doing a little "memory lane."
- While I still got one.

184
00:14:56,474 --> 00:15:00,308
- Mira, Rolando wants to talk to you.
- Carlito, I gotta get back to the game.

185
00:15:00,394 --> 00:15:03,113
You need anything, bodyguard,
anything, call me, okay?

186
00:15:03,194 --> 00:15:05,788
- You call me. Take care.
- Pachanga. Good to see you.

187
00:15:06,394 --> 00:15:09,272
- Rolando?
- S. He's around the corner.

188
00:15:10,434 --> 00:15:12,948
Guajiro, wait here for me.

189
00:15:13,034 --> 00:15:15,628
- In about five minutes, I'll be back.
- Sure, Carlito.

190
00:15:15,994 --> 00:15:18,064
Who is that? New back-up man?

191
00:15:18,194 --> 00:15:20,833
He's my little cousin.
I gotta visit my aunt later.

192
00:15:22,514 --> 00:15:24,106
Carlito, mi socio.

193
00:15:24,754 --> 00:15:26,107
Qu chvere!

194
00:15:28,634 --> 00:15:31,194
I said a prayer for you
while you were inside...

195
00:15:31,314 --> 00:15:33,828
...that harm will come
to him who harmed you.

196
00:15:34,114 --> 00:15:36,389
- Thank you.
- Sintate. Sit down.

197
00:15:39,834 --> 00:15:42,189
- You are well?
- Well enough.

198
00:15:42,754 --> 00:15:44,870
You look like you're doing good
for yourself.

199
00:15:45,274 --> 00:15:47,310
Why not? Business is good.

200
00:15:47,994 --> 00:15:50,747
- Smack.
- The coca business.

201
00:15:51,474 --> 00:15:53,908
That's all there is. Heroin is dead.

202
00:15:54,554 --> 00:15:57,671
- But you know all of this, right?
- No, I didn't know that.

203
00:16:07,514 --> 00:16:09,789
Let's speak the truth between us.

204
00:16:10,794 --> 00:16:13,592
You did five years
and never once mentioned my name.

205
00:16:14,154 --> 00:16:17,146
I know that you could have given me up...

206
00:16:17,554 --> 00:16:20,751
...and made things easier for yourself,
but you didn't.

207
00:16:21,074 --> 00:16:23,110
Muy bien hecho. Good for you.

208
00:16:24,594 --> 00:16:27,392
But you see I got rich
while you were inside.

209
00:16:27,714 --> 00:16:30,069
Maybe you think I owe you?

210
00:16:31,354 --> 00:16:33,424
I don't want anything from you.

211
00:16:33,714 --> 00:16:37,024
- Who are you working with?
- I ain't working with nobody.

212
00:16:37,394 --> 00:16:39,908
- Nobody?
- I'm retired.

213
00:16:40,514 --> 00:16:42,232
- Retired?
- That's right.

214
00:16:42,514 --> 00:16:43,708
Retired?

215
00:16:46,914 --> 00:16:47,983
You're serious?

216
00:16:48,074 --> 00:16:50,747
I'm serious. That's right. I'm out. I quit.

217
00:16:51,394 --> 00:16:55,990
So, Carlito Brigante got religion, right?

218
00:16:57,234 --> 00:16:59,748
That's right. I'm studying to be a priest.

219
00:17:04,954 --> 00:17:06,672
So what are you doing these days?

220
00:17:06,754 --> 00:17:09,632
Nothing much. I'm still in school.

221
00:17:10,314 --> 00:17:12,111
I got a job though.

222
00:17:12,194 --> 00:17:13,946
No kidding. Doing what?

223
00:17:14,034 --> 00:17:16,992
Just a little legwork
for Seor Pablo Cabrales.

224
00:17:17,434 --> 00:17:19,026
- Cabrales.
- Yeah.

225
00:17:19,274 --> 00:17:22,152
What do you want to do that shit for?
That's not good.

226
00:17:22,274 --> 00:17:25,072
Come on, Carlito.
I'm not making a career out of it.

227
00:17:25,154 --> 00:17:27,304
I'm a delivery boy, that's all.

228
00:17:27,554 --> 00:17:29,033
Check this out.

229
00:17:30,634 --> 00:17:32,192
That's $30,000.

230
00:17:39,834 --> 00:17:41,870
Can I ask you for a favor?

231
00:17:42,874 --> 00:17:43,989
What's that?

232
00:17:44,194 --> 00:17:47,504
I gotta go down the block for this pickup.
Can you come with me?

233
00:17:48,674 --> 00:17:52,064
Come on. Don't get me involved
with that stuff.

234
00:17:52,154 --> 00:17:54,748
Come on. I know these guys.
They're friends.

235
00:17:54,834 --> 00:17:56,392
I just wanna walk in with you.

