Come on, Frankie.

1187
01:34:01,434 --> 01:34:03,823
Your daddy's waitin' for ya.

1188
01:34:06,354 --> 01:34:07,389
Come on!

1189
01:34:07,834 --> 01:34:10,826
Take an end, for Christ's sake.
We're fallin' out of position.

1190
01:34:11,474 --> 01:34:14,272
We're gonna stand you up
and say good night.

1191
01:34:18,474 --> 01:34:19,907
Get him on the other side.

1192
01:34:20,074 --> 01:34:23,589
One, two, three.

1193
01:34:39,194 --> 01:34:42,584
There's a line you cross
you don't never come back from.

1194
01:34:44,274 --> 01:34:45,912
Point of no return.

1195
01:34:46,994 --> 01:34:50,703
Dave crossed it. I'm here with him.

1196
01:34:51,474 --> 01:34:54,864
That means I'm goin' along for the ride,
the whole ride...

1197
01:34:55,194 --> 01:34:58,470
...all the way to the end of the line,
wherever that is.

1198
01:35:02,474 --> 01:35:05,307
I had to do it.
He never would've let me live.

1199
01:35:06,634 --> 01:35:09,546
I know, you're pissed.
I'm gonna throw in another $10,000.

1200
01:35:09,634 --> 01:35:13,309
I'm gonna send over the whole $60,000
in cash tomorrow. All right?

1201
01:35:13,994 --> 01:35:18,272
It's gonna look like the kid tried to spring
the old man, boat flipped, they drowned.

1202
01:35:18,354 --> 01:35:22,666
Maybe they got their heads split
by a scow or barge just for good measure.

1203
01:35:22,794 --> 01:35:25,388
This is never gonna come back to us.
Trust me.

1204
01:35:25,594 --> 01:35:27,824
- You ripped him off, didn't you?
- Who?

1205
01:35:28,234 --> 01:35:31,510
Tony T. You did take the million dollars,
didn't you?

1206
01:35:37,234 --> 01:35:38,303
Yeah.

1207
01:35:43,514 --> 01:35:46,904
You ain't a lawyer no more, Dave.
You're a gangster now.

1208
01:35:47,754 --> 01:35:50,826
You're on the other side.
Whole new ball game.

1209
01:35:52,514 --> 01:35:57,269
You can't learn about it in school,
and you can't have a late start.

1210
01:35:58,634 --> 01:36:00,352
Don't worry about me.

1211
01:36:00,914 --> 01:36:02,393
One more thing.

1212
01:36:03,994 --> 01:36:05,268
We're even.

1213
01:36:07,154 --> 01:36:08,667
- Let's get a drink.
- Say it!

1214
01:36:11,674 --> 01:36:12,993
We're even.

1215
01:36:15,914 --> 01:36:17,188
We're even.

1216
01:36:24,834 --> 01:36:27,109
We ain't never gonna sell these tickets...

1217
01:36:27,954 --> 01:36:29,990
...whackin' a boss and his kid.

1218
01:36:32,594 --> 01:36:35,427
These Italians, I work with 'em, I know 'em.

1219
01:36:36,074 --> 01:36:38,986
They will read this one
with their eyes closed.

1220
01:36:40,234 --> 01:36:41,906
I gotta keep movin'.

1221
01:37:23,474 --> 01:37:24,907
Most people will.

1222
01:37:31,314 --> 01:37:32,542
You get old enough...

1223
01:37:32,634 --> 01:37:35,785
...you remember a reason
why everybody wants to whack you.

1224
01:37:36,034 --> 01:37:37,706
You believe 'em all...

1225
01:37:39,194 --> 01:37:41,788
...but you know somebody's gotta be lyin'.

1226
01:37:43,274 --> 01:37:45,424
Or maybe they're all lyin'.

1227
01:37:47,354 --> 01:37:51,666
When you can't see the angles no more,
you're in trouble, baby.

1228
01:37:52,834 --> 01:37:53,983
You're in trouble.

1229
01:37:59,314 --> 01:38:01,987
There's a Patrolman Williams on the line.

1230
01:38:03,594 --> 01:38:04,913
Put him on.

1231
01:38:06,474 --> 01:38:10,786
Mr. Kleinfeld? This is Patrolman Williams.
We're down here at your garage.

1232
01:38:11,594 --> 01:38:14,108
Your license plate is DK 777?

1233
01:38:14,434 --> 01:38:16,152
Yeah. Is there a problem?

1234
01:38:16,234 --> 01:38:19,863
Somebody tried to steal your Mercedes.
There was an accident.

1235
01:38:20,154 --> 01:38:22,031
- There was an accident?
- Yeah.

1236
01:38:22,114 --> 01:38:24,708
- Is it badly damaged?
- I'm afraid so.

1237
01:38:24,794 --> 01:38:26,546
I'll be right down.

1238
01:38:35,514 --> 01:38:37,550
I'll be ten minutes. Come on.

1239
01:39:50,914 --> 01:39:53,428
Mr. Taglialucci says to hold that for him!

1240
01:40:08,354 --> 01:40:09,503
Wait up.

1241
01:40:10,274 --> 01:40:12,788
I can't talk. I have an appointment.

1242
01:40:13,674 --> 01:40:17,633
You were right about Kleinfeld.
He's a bad guy.

1243
01:40:18,234 --> 01:40:21,988
- Me and him are finished.
- I can't talk. I'll call you, okay?

1244
01:40:22,074 --> 01:40:23,905
Slow down. What is it?

1245
01:40:24,794 --> 01:40:27,388
- Am I on the outs with you? Is that it?
- Yeah.

1246
01:40:27,474 --> 01:40:29,669
That's crazy. What's wrong with you?

1247
01:40:29,754 --> 01:40:32,427
I have a lot on my mind.
Can we please talk later?

1248
01:40:32,554 --> 01:40:36,024
I just wanted you to know
you were right about Kleinfeld.

1249
01:40:36,554 --> 01:40:39,193
- I'm sorry if you're upset.
- I gotta go.

1250
01:40:39,314 --> 01:40:40,872
I have a doctor's appointment.

1251
01:40:40,954 --> 01:40:43,832
- What's the matter? You sick?
- No, I'm late.

1252
01:40:44,474 --> 01:40:49,150
- We'll take a cab. What's wrong?
- No, Charlie, I'm late! I'm late!

1253
01:40:51,994 --> 01:40:54,508
- You mean you...
- Not for long, okay?

1254
01:40:56,394 --> 01:40:57,827
What does that mean?

1255
01:40:57,914 --> 01:41:00,667
I'm not gonna have a kid
who's not gonna have a father.

1256
01:41:01,474 --> 01:41:03,385
We gotta talk about this.

1257
01:41:05,354 --> 01:41:07,948
- Mr. Brigante, my name is Duncan.
- Oh, my God.

1258
01:41:08,034 --> 01:41:11,743
I'm here to escort you to Mr. Norwalk
in the District Attorney's office.

1259
01:41:12,154 --> 01:41:15,226
I got nothin' to say to him
unless I'm under arrest.

1260
01:41:15,314 --> 01:41:18,545
Mr. Norwalk has a tape
he'd like to play for you.

1261
01:41:19,514 --> 01:41:23,951
Unless I'm under arrest, I ain't goin'
anywhere, especially without my lawyer.

1262
01:41:24,874 --> 01:41:28,503
Mr. Kleinfeld took a knife in the chest
at 2:00 this afternoon.

1263
01:41:31,514 --> 01:41:33,630
I advise you to come with us.

1264
01:41:34,434 --> 01:41:36,948
We may be the only friends you've got.

1265
01:41:38,874 --> 01:41:40,307
I'm going, too.

1266
01:41:41,474 --> 01:41:43,510
Kleinfeld's lucky to be alive.

1267
01:41:44,354 --> 01:41:46,345
We're holding him at East Side Hospital.

1268
01:41:46,434 --> 01:41:49,232
We want his ass healthy
when we send it upstate.

1269
01:41:49,754 --> 01:41:52,507
You're sendin' him upstate? What for?

1270
01:41:54,314 --> 01:41:57,863
David Kleinfeld became a very big fish
while you were gone.

1271
01:41:59,274 --> 01:42:01,151
Even bigger than you. He's dirty.

1272
01:42:01,234 --> 01:42:05,671
Money laundering, jury tampering, bribery.
We've been after him for some time now.

1273
01:42:06,714 --> 01:42:09,182
I don't know nothin' about that, so...

1274
01:42:10,514 --> 01:42:12,630
There's a lot you don't know.

1275
01:42:14,834 --> 01:42:17,667
Bill, you got no case here.
You know it and I know it.

1276
01:42:17,754 --> 01:42:19,870
Chances are, you won't even
get an indictment.

1277
01:42:19,954 --> 01:42:21,672
Wanna try your luck?

1278
01:42:22,394 --> 01:42:26,626
Look, let's not both waste our time.
You said maybe I could help myself.

1279
01:42:26,994 --> 01:42:30,509
- You're not taping this, are you?
- Gimme a little credit.

1280
01:42:30,594 --> 01:42:33,631
All right. I thought of something
you might want.

1281
01:42:34,554 --> 01:42:37,830
You get off me, I'll help you put
Carlito Brigante back inside.

1282
01:42:37,914 --> 01:42:39,711
Brigante? For what?

1283
01:42:40,954 --> 01:42:45,584
After he got out, he started coming to
my office and making a lot of phone calls.

1284
01:42:45,714 --> 01:42:50,344
I found out he was back with Rolando
Rivas, his old partner, dealin' coke.

1285
01:42:51,394 --> 01:42:53,191
And I'm talkin' serious numbers.

1286
01:42:53,874 --> 01:42:55,705
Would you testify to that?

1287
01:42:56,754 --> 01:42:58,028
Absolutely.

1288
01:43:02,874 --> 01:43:04,307
We don't believe him.

1289
01:43:07,514 --> 01:43:12,144
Word on the street is you've been clean
since you came out of prison.

1290
01:43:13,234 --> 01:43:15,190
Kleinfeld's the one we're after.

1291
01:43:15,834 --> 01:43:19,668
He was right. I'd never get
an indictment with what I had.

1292
01:43:20,274 --> 01:43:22,185
But now, with your help...

1293
01:43:23,154 --> 01:43:25,952
...we can put this filth away
for a long time.

1294
01:43:30,154 --> 01:43:31,109
Hermano...

1295
01:43:32,914 --> 01:43:34,870
...we know about Tony T.

1296
01:43:35,594 --> 01:43:37,027
Who's Tony T.?

1297
01:43:37,554 --> 01:43:38,907
Yeah, right.

1298
01:43:39,714 --> 01:43:43,992
His body popped up in the East River
yesterday, and his kid, Frankie's.

1299
01:43:44,954 --> 01:43:47,832
Somebody was trying
to bust Tony outta prison.

1300
01:43:48,474 --> 01:43:52,023
I don't know these people you mentioned.
I don't know them.

1301
01:43:53,554 --> 01:43:56,751
Tony T. had another son
besides Frankie, Vincent.

1302
01:43:57,674 --> 01:44:00,347
Seems Vincent went crazy
after those bodies popped up.

1303
01:44:00,594 --> 01:44:04,030
Let it out all over the street
that Kleinfeld set up that prison break...

1304
01:44:04,114 --> 01:44:06,309
...then killed his father and his brother.

1305
01:44:07,034 --> 01:44:09,264
We aren't saying you were
on that boat too.

1306
01:44:10,274 --> 01:44:14,153
But knowing your relationship
with Kleinfeld, that's a good possibility.

1307
01:44:14,234 --> 01:44:16,190
Don't you think, hermano?

1308
01:44:17,234 --> 01:44:18,872
I don't like boats.

1309
01:44:21,674 --> 01:44:23,551
All right, here's the deal.

1310
01:44:23,794 --> 01:44:26,786
If you were on that boat,
and I know goddamn well you were...

1311
01:44:27,314 --> 01:44:30,386
...testify against Kleinfeld
for first-degree murder.

1312
01:44:32,354 --> 01:44:36,029
You'll receive complete immunity and
a couple airline tickets to the Bahamas.

1313
01:44:36,114 --> 01:44:39,504
You wanna get even with Kleinfeld?
Here it is on a silver platter.

1314
01:44:40,314 --> 01:44:44,307
I would love to help you, but I can't.
I don't know what you're talking about.

1315
01:44:44,394 --> 01:44:47,431
I don't know these people.
I don't know what you're sayin'...

1316
01:44:47,714 --> 01:44:51,024
Let me tell you somethin',
Mr. Convicted Dope Peddler...

1317
01:44:51,114 --> 01:44:54,868
...if we can guess you were on that boat,
how long before the Italians do, too?

1318
01:44:54,954 --> 01:44:57,627
What if they get to Kleinfeld?
They can twist his arm.

1319
01:44:57,754 --> 01:44:59,949
You think he won't give you up?
Think again!

1320
01:45:00,074 --> 01:45:02,747
You don't owe Kleinfeld nothing.

1321
01:45:03,074 --> 01:45:06,544
The shyster tried to set you up.
Bury you, Jack.

1322
01:45:12,154 --> 01:45:13,348
That it?

1323
01:45:19,074 --> 01:45:21,383
I wanna hear from you by noon tomorrow.

1324
01:45:21,554 --> 01:45:25,024
You think you're gonna sail off
into the sunset, asshole?

1325
01:45:25,714 --> 01:45:27,067
Think again.

1326
01:45:32,354 --> 01:45:36,347
You gotta do it.
They're giving you no choice.

1327
01:45:37,234 --> 01:45:39,031
You want out, go ahead.

1328
01:45:39,194 --> 01:45:41,947
You can turn around,
walk away, never look back.

1329
01:45:42,034 --> 01:45:44,628
I would understand. But I got a plan.

1330
01:45:45,194 --> 01:45:48,106
I got a way outta this.
Pull over here, please.

1331
01:45:48,434 --> 01:45:51,267
- What's going on?
- Just wait five minutes.

1332
01:45:53,514 --> 01:45:56,551
- Where are you going?
- Wait here five minutes.

1333
01:46:48,914 --> 01:46:50,347
What is that?

1334
01:46:50,554 --> 01:46:53,591
Tickets on an overnight train to Miami.

1335
01:46:54,874 --> 01:46:56,944
Nobody's gonna look for us on the train.

1336
01:46:57,034 --> 01:47:00,071
We hit Miami, we catch a plane to Nassau.

1337
01:47:01,674 --> 01:47:04,142
- What about the club? Your money?
- Fuck the club.

1338
01:47:04,234 --> 01:47:08,944
I already got $70,000 in a safe. My friend
in the islands can float us the rest.

1339
01:47:09,594 --> 01:47:12,904
Let's do it. Let's get outta here.

1340
01:47:13,834 --> 01:47:15,347
All three of us.

1341
01:47:18,154 --> 01:47:19,906
We're runnin' out of time, babe.

1342
01:47:20,154 --> 01:47:24,147
The dream don't come no closer by itself.
We gotta run after it now.

1343
01:47:27,834 --> 01:47:31,713
I know, it's not the way I planned it either,
but it is how it is.

1344
01:47:32,514 --> 01:47:36,871
I'm gonna go to the club, get my money,
and I'm goin' straight to Grand Central.

1345
01:47:36,954 --> 01:47:40,867
Train leaves 11:30 for Miami.
You're gonna be there, Gail?

1346
01:47:42,274 --> 01:47:44,105
- You'll be there?
- I'll be there.

1347
01:47:44,194 --> 01:47:46,025
I love you.

1348
01:47:49,354 --> 01:47:52,187
- Just make sure you're there.
- I'll see you later.

1349
01:47:55,794 --> 01:47:59,548
Train leaves in five hours,
and I'm angling like crazy in my head.

1350
01:48:00,034 --> 01:48:05,062
Norwalk'll blow over. He won't come out
of the country if he can't bust me here.

1351
01:48:05,714 --> 01:48:07,830
But he ain't my only problem.

1352
01:48:08,274 --> 01:48:10,993
Five hours left. Can I think of everything?

1353
01:48:11,114 --> 01:48:13,833
Cover everybody. Tie all the shoelaces.

1354
01:48:16,114 --> 01:48:17,911
Gotta listen to my instincts...

1355
01:48:17,994 --> 01:48:21,589
...like the one tellin' me that face
and that uniform don't go together.

1356
01:48:24,714 --> 01:48:28,468
Just one last piece of business.
Gotta look in Kleinfeld's eyes.

1357
01:48:28,954 --> 01:48:30,626
Gotta know for sure.

1358
01:48:38,994 --> 01:48:40,222
Who are you?

1359
01:48:40,354 --> 01:48:43,391
- Kleinfeld is my lawyer.
- Hands on the wall.

1360
01:48:49,594 --> 01:48:50,788
Go ahead.

1361
01:48:57,794 --> 01:48:58,749
Relax.

1362
01:49:00,274 --> 01:49:01,707
It's your pal.

1363
01:49:03,234 --> 01:49:05,190
Scared the hell out of me.

1364
01:49:06,234 --> 01:49:10,022
Cop's not supposed to let anybody in.
It's you, it's okay, but...

1365
01:49:10,354 --> 01:49:12,470
Cops ain't gonna protect you.

1366
01:49:13,634 --> 01:49:15,386
The mob is looking for you.

1367
01:49:16,354 --> 01:49:18,743
I know. Where the fuck have you been?

1368
01:49:18,834 --> 01:49:20,313
What do you got here?

1369
01:49:24,514 --> 01:49:26,505
- Where you been?
- How do you feel?

1370
01:49:26,594 --> 01:49:29,904
I'm not feeling very well.
Where the fuck have you been?

1371
01:49:35,394 --> 01:49:37,305
I've been to Norwalk's office.

1372
01:49:38,514 --> 01:49:39,788
I heard the tape.

1373
01:49:41,994 --> 01:49:43,188
That pig.

1374
01:49:44,514 --> 01:49:47,267
Never give up your friends,
no matter what.

1375
01:49:48,914 --> 01:49:51,872
They doctor these things,
play 'em outta context.

1376
01:49:52,154 --> 01:49:53,826
I can't believe you are such a...

1377
01:49:54,114 --> 01:49:56,105
Don't fuckin' do that! Fuck you!

1378
01:49:57,594 --> 01:49:59,664
What the fuck are you doing?

1379
01:50:00,794 --> 01:50:03,467
Would you fuckin' put that away?
It's loaded!

1380
01:50:07,554 --> 01:50:11,706
Fuck you and your self-righteous code
of the goddamned street.

1381
01:50:13,154 --> 01:50:17,386
Did it pull you out of a thirty-year stint
in five years? Did it? No, I did.

1382
01:50:18,594 --> 01:50:21,870
Did it get you acquitted four fucking times?
No, it didn't. I did.

1383
01:50:21,954 --> 01:50:25,151
So fuck you, fuck the street.
Your whole goddamn world's this big...

1384
01:50:25,234 --> 01:50:28,146
...and there's only one rule:
you save your own ass.

1385
01:50:33,914 --> 01:50:35,472
Save your own ass.

1386
01:50:36,754 --> 01:50:40,872
- Save your own ass.
- See this? It belongs here.

1387
01:50:41,474 --> 01:50:44,864
Not behind a pillow.
This way you can reach for it quick.

1388
01:50:45,674 --> 01:50:47,904
They come in, you ready for 'em.

1389
01:50:49,994 --> 01:50:53,304
So long. You got a beautiful future.

1390
01:51:30,234 --> 01:51:31,667
Quittin' time.

1391
01:51:31,794 --> 01:51:34,752
- You're early.
- A few minutes. Finish your paper?

1392
01:51:34,834 --> 01:51:36,790
- It's all yours.
- Thanks.

1393
01:51:38,114 --> 01:51:39,308
Be good.

1394
01:51:53,834 --> 01:51:56,223
There's a delivery for you, Mr. Kleinfeld.

1395
01:51:56,954 --> 01:51:59,673
- From who?
- From my father...

1396
01:52:00,634 --> 01:52:02,113
...and my brother.

1397
01:52:05,234 --> 01:52:06,792
Adis, counselor.

1398
01:52:23,994 --> 01:52:27,225
Where the hell you been?
You know somebody tried to kill Kleinfeld?

1399
01:52:27,314 --> 01:52:31,466
I heard about it. Listen, me and Gail
are goin' out of town for a couple days.

1400
01:52:31,594 --> 01:52:34,188
- You're gonna get married.
- Listen to me.

1401
01:52:34,394 --> 01:52:38,672
I want you to go to Gail's house,
pick her up, drive her to Grand Central.

1402
01:52:38,754 --> 01:52:41,427
I want you to wait with her there for me.

1403
01:52:41,714 --> 01:52:45,423
Train leaves 11:30 sharp.
We can't miss this train, understand?

1404
01:52:45,754 --> 01:52:47,551
You got me? Go ahead.

1405
01:53:08,074 --> 01:53:09,951
It's me, Pete Amadesso.

1406
01:53:10,034 --> 01:53:13,231
- Remember me?
- How ya doin'?

1407
01:53:13,794 --> 01:53:15,671
- Good.
- What're you doin' here?

1408
01:53:15,834 --> 01:53:19,588
We heard this was your joint.
Nice! Come by to say "hello."

1409
01:53:19,714 --> 01:53:21,944
Good to see you. How you doin'?

1410
01:53:22,114 --> 01:53:24,503
- Good to see you. Yeah, long time.
- Long time.

1411
01:53:24,594 --> 01:53:26,312
Sit down. Have a drink with us.

1412
01:53:26,394 --> 01:53:28,464
Come on. Sit down.

1413
01:53:30,914 --> 01:53:34,543
I said: "Shit, I ain't seen Carlito
in what, fifteen years?"

1414
01:53:35,074 --> 01:53:36,905
Fifteen. Yeah, gotta be. Sure.

1415
01:53:36,994 --> 01:53:38,871
- Long time.
- Long fuckin' time.

1416
01:53:39,114 --> 01:53:42,186
- Sorry. Joe Battaglia.
- My pleasure. Good to see you.

1417
01:53:42,274 --> 01:53:43,787
Sonny Manzanero.

1418
01:53:44,234 --> 01:53:46,111
- How ya doin'?
- Carlito Brigante.

1419
01:53:47,474 --> 01:53:50,910
Me and Carlito used to push
a little skag back in '57, '58.

1420
01:53:51,194 --> 01:53:52,832
Couple of fuckin' kids.

1421
01:53:53,354 --> 01:53:56,266
First time I saw this guy,
I thought he was Italian!

1422
01:53:57,714 --> 01:53:58,669
Look at him!

1423
01:53:58,794 --> 01:54:00,113
Shit!

1424
01:54:00,994 --> 01:54:04,111
Pete Amadesso walks into my club
just like that.

1425
01:54:04,674 --> 01:54:05,743
Bullshit.

1426
01:54:05,834 --> 01:54:08,473
There's an angle here. Pete's a made guy.

1427
01:54:08,554 --> 01:54:11,512
His uncle's a heavy hitter
with the Pleasant Avenue bunch.

1428
01:54:11,594 --> 01:54:15,223
What's he doin' here?
Probably Tony T.'s people sent him.

1429
01:54:16,554 --> 01:54:19,466
Maybe he's watchin' me, seein' if I break.

1430
01:54:20,714 --> 01:54:22,591
Waitin' for me to panic.

1431
01:54:24,234 --> 01:54:27,146
They still don't know for sure
if I was on that boat.

1432
01:54:27,234 --> 01:54:29,464
They think, but they don't know.

1433
01:54:30,354 --> 01:54:33,710
'Cause if they knew, I'd already be dead.

1434
01:54:35,194 --> 01:54:38,391
Right now, they just watchin' me.

1435
01:54:38,914 --> 01:54:42,429
He was always one of us.
That was a guy. That's who he is.

1436
01:54:42,954 --> 01:54:44,546
And we gotta know that.

1437
01:54:44,994 --> 01:54:46,950
So anyway, so I says to the guy:

1438
01:54:47,754 --> 01:54:51,542
"Tommy, Carlito ain't no fuckin' nigger.
Look at the way he dances!"

1439
01:54:53,834 --> 01:54:55,825
He dances like an Italian!

1440
01:54:57,074 --> 01:55:01,386
You should see him do the tarantella!
Waiter, get over here.

1441
01:55:02,514 --> 01:55:05,870
Bring these guys the best champagne
we got on the house.

1442
01:55:06,194 --> 01:55:08,947
- Where you goin'? Stay with us.
- I'm a workin' man.

1443
01:55:09,034 --> 01:55:11,468
Let me do what I gotta do.
I'll be right back.

1444
01:55:11,594 --> 01:55:12,583
Okay, buddy.

1445
01:55:48,834 --> 01:55:49,983
Motherfucker!

1446
01:55:53,794 --> 01:55:54,783
Fuck.

1447
01:56:05,274 --> 01:56:06,548
You seen the guy?

1448
01:56:09,634 --> 01:56:10,703
Saso.

1449
01:56:52,034 --> 01:56:54,184
- Where's my money?
- What're you talking about?

1450
01:56:54,274 --> 01:56:55,707
- Where's my money?
- I don't know.

1451
01:56:55,794 --> 01:56:59,230
You heard Kleinfeld got whacked,
so you figured I was dead, too!

1452
01:56:59,434 --> 01:57:02,665
- You thought you inherited my money?
- I swear...

1453
01:57:02,794 --> 01:57:05,592
Where's my money?
I'll cut your fuckin' liver out!

1454
01:57:05,834 --> 01:57:07,108
Okay. Okay.

1455
01:57:07,714 --> 01:57:11,229
It's in the box, under the register.
I was gonna tell you.

1456
01:57:18,154 --> 01:57:20,349
I want you to meet a good friend of mine.

1457
01:57:25,714 --> 01:57:28,592
You ever hear of Vinnie's father,
Tony Taglialucci?

1458
01:57:30,314 --> 01:57:33,067
Tony T. Yeah, he passed away recently.
Sorry about that.

1459
01:57:33,554 --> 01:57:36,022
I hear your Jew lawyer
met with an accident.

1460
01:57:36,194 --> 01:57:38,754
I haven't seen him lately. What is this?

1461
01:57:40,114 --> 01:57:42,992
I told you bring the best out,
you bring me this cheap shit?

1462
01:57:43,074 --> 01:57:44,223
Come on. Excuse me.

1463
01:57:46,394 --> 01:57:49,511
- Vinnie, slow down.
- "Ain't seen him lately!" The lyin' fuck!

1464
01:57:49,594 --> 01:57:53,143
- Seen him in the hospital!
- We'll take him outside. Sit down.

1465
01:58:00,554 --> 01:58:02,306
Relax, we'll get him.

1466
01:58:37,994 --> 01:58:39,791
Where the hell is he?

1467
01:58:49,994 --> 01:58:53,350
- The little fuckin' spic bastard!
- Where you going, man?

1468
01:58:53,554 --> 01:58:57,342
- Nobody gets back here!
- Damn it, get the fuck out of here!

1469
01:59:03,674 --> 01:59:06,268
Come on, let's go. We'll get him outside.

1470
01:59:16,154 --> 01:59:17,951
There he is! Come on!

1471
02:00:36,394 --> 02:00:37,907
What do you want me to do?

1472
02:00:40,594 --> 02:00:42,232
I can't do nothin'.

1473
02:01:03,074 --> 02:01:04,666
Get the fuck off!

1474
02:01:30,194 --> 02:01:33,584
Attention, ladies and gentlemen.
Final boarding on Track 17.

1475
02:01:33,674 --> 02:01:36,552
All reserved on the 11:20
Amtrak Merchant's Limited.

1476
02:01:36,634 --> 02:01:39,512
Train number 1-7-9
bound for Washington, D. C...

1477
02:01:39,634 --> 02:01:44,025
...serving Newark, Menlo Park, Trenton,
Philadelphia, Aberdeen and Baltimore.

1478
02:01:44,114 --> 02:01:45,433
All aboard!

1479
02:02:38,874 --> 02:02:40,466
Get the fuck out!

1480
02:03:14,194 --> 02:03:15,263
Cover the doors.

1481
02:03:35,714 --> 02:03:38,023
Did you see that one? The one in the blue?

1482
02:03:39,194 --> 02:03:41,105
You guys are dogs. Dogs!

1483
02:03:58,034 --> 02:03:59,945
Now boarding on Track 19.

1484
02:04:00,034 --> 02:04:04,425
All reserved on the 11:30 Amtrak
Silver Star bound for Tampa and Miami.

1485
02:04:04,954 --> 02:04:08,344
Maybe we should wait by the train.

1486
02:04:08,914 --> 02:04:10,472
Sounds good to me.

1487
02:04:12,794 --> 02:04:14,113
Come on, Charlie.

1488
02:04:22,074 --> 02:04:25,623
I'm goin' to the Bronx IRT uptown.
Which way I go for that?

1489
02:04:25,794 --> 02:04:28,388
You'll take a right here,
shoot down the alley...

1490
02:04:28,594 --> 02:04:31,506
...and up the stairs. Can't miss it.
- Thanks.

1491
02:04:50,634 --> 02:04:52,067
There he is!

1492
02:05:20,154 --> 02:05:21,667
Vinnie, wait up.

1493
02:05:40,954 --> 02:05:43,707
He ain't up here. Let's go down. Come on.

1494
02:05:44,554 --> 02:05:45,828
All right.

1495
02:06:00,474 --> 02:06:03,944
Attention, ladies and gentlemen.
Now boarding on Track 12...

1496
02:06:04,234 --> 02:06:08,432
...all reserved on the 11:45
Amtrak Senator, train Number 1-7-6.

1497
02:06:09,194 --> 02:06:12,027
Bound for Boston
and serving Stamford, Bridgeport...

1498
02:06:12,114 --> 02:06:15,072
...New London, Cambridge,
Kingston and Providence.

1499
02:06:27,274 --> 02:06:30,983
Attention, ladies and gentlemen.
Last call, Track 19...

1500
02:06:31,474 --> 02:06:34,989
...the 11:30 Amtrak Silver Star
bound for Tampa and Miami.

1501
02:06:35,194 --> 02:06:36,513
All aboard!

1502
02:06:51,074 --> 02:06:52,826
He's not down here.

1503
02:07:02,554 --> 02:07:06,024
- We lost him.
- We didn't fuckin' lose him. He's up top.

1504
02:07:06,354 --> 02:07:08,265
Did you hear me? Move!

1505
02:07:54,194 --> 02:07:55,183
He's there!

1506
02:08:16,634 --> 02:08:18,113
I'll kill you!

1507
02:08:23,354 --> 02:08:26,152
Motherfucker! I'll kill ya!

1508
02:08:48,834 --> 02:08:50,267
Stop! Police!

1509
02:08:52,074 --> 02:08:54,713
The train's gonna leave! Come on, man!

1510
02:08:57,754 --> 02:08:58,982
Come on!

1511
02:09:00,074 --> 02:09:01,473
You made it!

1512
02:09:03,874 --> 02:09:04,909
That's him!

1513
02:09:11,154 --> 02:09:12,712
Police! Freeze!

1514
02:09:17,834 --> 02:09:19,506
It's gonna be okay.

1515
02:09:21,874 --> 02:09:22,943
Remember me?

1516
02:09:24,154 --> 02:09:26,145
Benny Blanco from the Bronx?

1517
02:09:42,834 --> 02:09:46,270
No hard feelings.
But I got to think about my future, too.

1518
02:09:47,514 --> 02:09:50,950
You know, it is that way sometimes, papi.
Come on, let's go.

1519
02:09:51,474 --> 02:09:52,623
No, you stay here.

1520
02:09:59,154 --> 02:10:00,633
Don't try to talk.

1521
02:10:01,234 --> 02:10:04,510
We're gonna get you to a hospital.
You're gonna be okay.

1522
02:10:04,594 --> 02:10:07,267
Just hold on, baby. Just hold on.

1523
02:10:08,834 --> 02:10:11,587
Hold on, baby. Please, hold on.

1524
02:10:13,634 --> 02:10:14,783
Take this.

1525
02:10:20,474 --> 02:10:22,988
Take it and get out.

1526
02:10:24,594 --> 02:10:25,913
Both of you.

1527
02:10:36,714 --> 02:10:38,193
You'll be okay.

1528
02:10:43,274 --> 02:10:46,391
Don't leave me, Charlie. Not yet.

1529
02:10:47,194 --> 02:10:49,628
Don't leave me, Charlie.

1530
02:10:51,474 --> 02:10:52,668
Don't go.

1531
02:11:04,794 --> 02:11:06,591
Please don't leave me.

1532
02:11:08,674 --> 02:11:09,868
Don't go.

1533
02:11:13,434 --> 02:11:15,311
You can't do this to me.

1534
02:11:17,394 --> 02:11:19,589
Oh, God. Don't leave me.

1535
02:12:04,674 --> 02:12:05,993
Sorry, boys...

1536
02:12:07,194 --> 02:12:10,664
...all the stitches in the world
can't sew me together again.

1537
02:12:11,994 --> 02:12:15,589
Lay down. Lay down.

1538
02:12:16,074 --> 02:12:19,623
Gonna stretch me out
in Fernandez Funeral Home on 109th St.

1539
02:12:20,994 --> 02:12:23,383
Always knew I'd make a stop there...

1540
02:12:24,234 --> 02:12:27,351
...but a lot later
than a whole gang of people thought.

1541
02:12:28,394 --> 02:12:30,146
Last of the Mo-Ricans.

1542
02:12:31,434 --> 02:12:33,345
Well, maybe not the last.

1543
02:12:35,834 --> 02:12:37,825
Gail's gonna be a good mom.

1544
02:12:38,714 --> 02:12:41,626
New, improved Carlito Brigante.

1545
02:12:43,714 --> 02:12:46,023
Hope she uses the money to get out.

1546
02:12:46,554 --> 02:12:49,432
No room in this city
for big hearts like hers.

1547
02:12:50,234 --> 02:12:51,508
Sorry, baby.

1548
02:12:52,874 --> 02:12:56,753
I tried the best I could. Honest.

1549
02:12:58,154 --> 02:13:00,748
Can't come with me on this trip, though.

1550
02:13:02,514 --> 02:13:04,232
Gettin' the shakes now.

1551
02:13:04,994 --> 02:13:08,589
Last call for drinks. Bar's closin' down.

1552
02:13:09,794 --> 02:13:11,386
Sun's out.

1553
02:13:12,154 --> 02:13:13,951
Where we goin' for breakfast?

1554
02:13:15,354 --> 02:13:17,026
Don't wanna go far.

1555
02:13:18,554 --> 02:13:19,873
Rough night.

1556
02:13:21,074 --> 02:13:22,348
Tired baby...

1557
02:13:23,794 --> 02:13:24,943
...tired.